      "content": "I see what you mean about tone, but it feels like you're judging them based on how they talk rather than what they actually know. Isn't it possible that 'professionalism' is just a code word for 'Standard English'? Like, if Candidate B was just a bit more formal, they'd be perfect, right? It seems like we're penalizing them just for using a different dialect even though they clearly have the skills.",
